				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Per-pixel and per-scanline aren't much different.  Per-pixel just means you divide up the scanlines into smaller sections if the PPU changes state while rendering a scanline.
<br />
<br />If you ever want to play Punch Out or Fire Emblem, you need per-pixel since the mapper switches CHR banks when it encounters a particular TILE number.</div>

					
