						<div class="postbody">Hardest part about more precision is breaking in and out of the loops. A lot harder to do scanline-&gt;pixel than frame-&gt;scanline.
<br />
<br />Say you load in tiledata for the next 8 pixels, but if you return from your loop, you lose that data. So you have to store it globally, or reload it for each pixel, the former being much more correct.
<br />
<br />But overall, not very hard. Weekend project or so.</div>

