					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I won't be so strict as to day that Per-frame rendering doesn't work with games that use scrolling in part of the screen.
<br />I mean, for example if your emu does per-frame rendering BUT records in which scanline(s) the scroll registers were modified, then, you can still make up your frame only once at the beggining of vblank and still fully support the partial screen scrolling.
<br />
<br />What I mean is there's not a single way of doing per-frame rendering, as there isn't a single way of doing per-scanline rendering.</div>

